<dt-example table-type="html-wide" order="1">

<css lib="datatables searchpane select" />
<js lib="jquery datatables searchpane select">
<![CDATA[

$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPane:{
            maxOptions: 5,
        },
    });
});

]]>
</js>

<title lib="SearchPane">Configuration option</title>

<info><![CDATA[

This is the SearchPane extension for DataTables. It allows results to be filtered based on the values of columns.

This example shows how the definition of the maxOptions config property can overcome having a low variance but still wanting a searchPane.

By setting the maxOptions values, any columns with less than that number of options will generate a searchpane.

]]></info>

